Abdominal tergite 1 (T1) with single transverse row of setae flanking distal edge, and one pair of short setae in antero-posterior margin; T2 with two parallel rows of setae in distal third of the tergite with regular distances between individual setae; T3 with three irregular rows of setae in distal half; T4‒5 with 4‒5 irregular rows of setae filling distal half of the tergite, setae in the most distal row longer; T6‒7 with 6‒7 irregular rows of setae occupying two-thirds of the tergite, setae in the most distal row longer; T8 with 4 irregular rows of setae in posterior half of tergite and with ten longer setae on the posterior edge (
Fig. 10
); T9 short, strongly sclerotized anteriorly and scarcely sclerotized posteriorly, well delimited from T 
